DOM(DOCUMENT OBJECT MODEL)
--IT is used in web development used to intract and manipulate(change)the html documents.

when the webpage loaded , the browser created DOM of the webpage

when the html file is loaded into the browser,
the javascript cannot understand the html document directly
DOM: it is basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree-like structure composed of object
keypoints:
1)Structure:The DOM represents the structure of HTML document as a each node in tree represents the elements,an attribute or text 
2)Manipulate:using javascript , you can intract with elements(buttons,paragraphs)on the webpage , changing the content , styles , can add or remove elements
3)event handling:you can handle the interactions , like click or pressing the button
4)W3C world wide web consortium

dom:
--document is the entry point of DOM 

<html>
<head>
<title>Mallareddy university<title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>i am in hyd</h1>
</body>
</html>

